<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Muffle" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Muffle,</orth> 1) to wrap, to cover by cloth or any garment: <bibl n="shak. luc 768" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 768</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.491" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 491</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.665" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 665</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.4.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 4, 41</bibl>. With <cit><quote>up:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 46</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 191</bibl>.
<lb />2) to blindfold: <cit><quote>will keep him --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 1, 100</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.134" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 134</bibl>. <cit><quote>love, whose view is --d still,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 177</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="750" />
